title: [Improvement][SQL] Performance optimization for a large number(10k) of tasks
body:
## Purpose of the pull request

Some database optimizations about scheduling

When a project contains 2k of processes and 3k of dependent nodes, the data volume of t_ds_task_instance/t_ds_relation_process_instance/t_ds_process_task_relation_log grows very fast, and running for a few days shows performance issues. Because of the lack of indexes, MasterServer scans dependent nodes and sub_process nodes It will cause serious performance problems in the database (eg: t_ds_task_instance has 200k records caused the 8c16g postgresql server CPU occupies 100%).

After optimization, the CPU usage of the database server is reduced to less than 10%.

## Brief change log

Add 3 indexes to the scheduler's database
